description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manchester Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Emergency Planning, Resilience and Response Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 8A Full time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen at MFT to join us as our &lt;strong&gt;Emergency Planning, &lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Resilience and Response Manager.&lt;/strong&gt; You will be leading your team to co-ordinate the delivery of an effective EPRR and business continuity function and will ensure emergency planning and resilience is an integral part of business planning, strategy and operations across the Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will ensure the legal and regulatory requirements that apply to the Trust are met including training, planning and co-ordination, working with NHSE/I, Local NHS Commissioners, multi-agency partners and the local resilience forum.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should be able to demonstrate that they meet the essential criteria for the role. Candidates should also have a good working knowledge of the Civil Contingencies Act 2004 and the NHS EPRR Framework 2015 and associated guidance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in the post, contact Carmel McBride Head of Delivery (Performance &amp; EPRR) 0161 276 5789 / 07815 654627 email: carmel.mcbride@mft.nhs.uk to arrange an informal discussion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameCarmel McBrideJob titleAssistant Director of PerformanceEmail addresscarmel.mcbride@mft.nhs.ukTelephone number0161 276 5789&lt;/p&gt;
